    "body": "### Problem\n\nSo, there is a project named [just](https://github.com/casey/just) that aims to do similar thing Make does. It does not seem to be currently recognized as a compiler. I checked my local install and no just.vim was available in the runtimepath. \n\nI made a quick config which seems to work, but I would like also someone else to verify that it is indeed complete and I did not miss anything.\n\n```vim\nif exists('current_compiler')\n    finish\nendif\nlet current_compiler = \"just\"\n\nCompilerSet makeprg=just\nCompilerSet errorformat&\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`just` is recognized as a valid compiler.",
